# Goal: run the full auto-calibrate sequence — move to cal_ready/standoff,
# wait for it to settle, optionally auto-center on the marker (see
# orchestrator's auto_center_enabled param — a standing YAML/param toggle
# set via the web app's set_parameters call, same pattern already used for
# ~/calibrate's planning_mode; not a per-call goal field, matching this
# project's convention of tuning via YAML params rather than per-call
# args), then call calibration_broadcaster_node's ~/calibrate action and
# relay its result. Empty for now, same reasoning as Calibrate.action's
# empty goal.
#
# Whether Stage 1 actually moves to cal_ready or instead calibrates from
# the arm's current pose is decided INTERNALLY by the node itself (see
# CalibrationOrchestratorNode::pending_manual_adjustment_'s doc comment,
# 2026-07-24) — not a per-call goal field. The single existing
# ~/start_auto_calibrate/~/auto_calibrate entry point behaves
# automatically based on that internal state (set when a previous
# auto-centering attempt failed, cleared once calibration completes or a
# preset-pose move happens) — no separate goal field or second
# button/service needed.
---
# Result: mirrors Calibrate.action's result fields, plus which stage failed
# if success is false (empty string on success).
bool success
string message
float64 max_spread_deg
float64 mean_spread_deg
# Empty on success. One of "cal_ready", "auto_center", "calibrate" —
# which stage of the sequence failed, for a caller (e.g. the web app) to
# show a more specific error than the generic message string alone.
string failed_stage
---
# Feedback: one line per stage transition, e.g. "Moving to cal_ready",
# "Auto-centering on marker", "Calibrating (sample 3/10)" — the last form
# mirrors Calibrate.action's feedback once that stage is reached, so a
# caller only listening to this action still sees per-sample progress.
string stage
uint32 samples_collected
uint32 samples_total